%N A341277 Number of length-n binary mesosome-avoiding strings.
%C A341277 A mesosome is a word of the form x x', where x' is a cyclic shift of x, different from x. A string is mesosome-avoiding if it has no subword (contiguous block) that is a mesosome.
%H A341277 Robert Israel, <a href="/A341277/b341277.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A341277 Robert Cummings, Jeffrey Shallit and Paul Staadecker, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2107.13813">Mesosome Avoidance</a>, arXiv:2107.13813 [cs.DM], 2021.
%H A341277 <a href="/index/Rec#order_10">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (2,-1,0,2,-4,2,0,-1,2,-1).
%F A341277 Let n = 4k + i for i = 0, 1, 2, 3 and n >= 5. Then:
%F A341277 a(4k    ) = (4k^3 + 15k^2 + 41k - 12)/3;
%F A341277 a(4k + 1) = (4k^3 + 18k^2 + 50k     )/3;
%F A341277 a(4k + 2) = (4k^3 + 21k^2 + 59k + 12)/3;
%F A341277 a(4k + 3) = (4k^3 + 24k^2 + 68k + 30)/3. [from 'Mesosome Avoidance', Theorem 2, eqn. (1), _Georg Fischer_, Nov 25 2022]
%F A341277 G.f.: (1 + x^2 + 2*x^3 + 4*x^5 - 4*x^6 - 2*x^7 - x^8 - 6*x^9 + 5*x^10 + 2*x^12 + 2*x^13 - 2*x^14)/((1-x)^2 * (1-x^4)^2). - _Robert Israel_, Nov 03 2025
%e A341277 For n = 4 the only strings not counted are 0110 and 1001.
%p A341277 f:= unapply((-I)^n/16 + (-I)^n*n*I/16 - 3*I*(-I)^n/16 + I^n/16 - I^n*n*I/16 + 3*I*I^n/16 + (-1)^n*n/32 - (11*(-1)^n)/32 + n^3/48 + (5*n^2)/16 + (325*n)/96 - 121/32,n);
%p A341277 f(0):= 1: f(1):= 2: f(3):= 8: f(4):= 14:
%p A341277 map(f, [$0..100]); # _Robert Israel_, Nov 03 2025
